author: Allan Jackson
title: GAS Head Yau Yee League
text:
GAS Head Yau Yee League Association football—Hong Kong By Allan Jackson | October 14, 2015 Last Updated: October 14, 2015 7:03 am < > 
Anxious moment as the Club Albion goalie, Jamie Devonshire come off his line but just misses this cross in their Yau Yee League-1 match with KCC Dragons at Sports Road on Sunday Oct 11. Albion edged the match 1-0. (Bill Cox/Epoch Times) 
HONG KONG—This weekend saw no games in either the HKFA Premier League or the First Division. 
In the second division, Sai Kung were 3-2 victors over Tuen Mun FC, and Sparta Rotterdam Mutual won 1-nil against Tsuen Wan. Sai Kung lead the table with a 100% record of 12 points from 4 matches, with Eastern District second with 10 points from 4 matches. 
In the third division, Central & Western were 7-1 victors over Rex Global North District, Fukien were 7-1 victors against King Mountain, Telecom won 3-2 against KCC, Sun International won 3-1 against Ornament, Hoi King were 1-nil winners against St Joseph’s, Islands won 2-nil against HKFYG, GFC Friends were 1-nil victors over KCDRSC, and Wing Go Fu Moon were 2-nil winners against New Fair Kui Tan. 
Central and Western and Hoi King lead the table with 100% records and 5 wins. 
Yau Yee League In the first division, Albion won 1-nil against KCC Dragons, Wanderers were 4-nil victors over Baker Tilly Spartans, GAS were 2-nil victors over USRC, Colts were 2-1 winners against The Store House Squadron, Swiss XI were 6-2 winners against Corinthians, and HKDC Mobsters were 5-1 victors over HKU70’s. 
GAS lead the table with a 100% record with 15 points from 5 matches, with Albion second on 12 points, and Wanderers and Colts joint third with 10 points, all from 5 matches.. 
In the second division, IUSC (Tai Po) drew nil-all against Colloids FC, IES won 1-nil against University, Azzurri drew nil-all against GGFC, Antonhill were 3-1 winners against The Store House Hearts, Boca Seniors were 5-2 victors over French Kiss, and KCC Knights were 1-nil victors over WYFC06. 
KCC Knights lead the table with 12 points, with IUSC (Tai Po) second on 11 points, and GGFC and Azzurri joint third with 10 points, all from 5 matches. 
In the third division, Dynamo won 4-2 against HKUSA, Grasshoppers were2-nil winners against HKSS, HOB were 5-2 victors over CAPS, White Youth won 5-2 against Green Cypress FC, Yan Po were 2-1 winners against Goal Visio, and ANP were 4-1 winners against CSOB. 
Dynamo lead the third division table with a 100% record and 15 points from 5 matches, with HOB in second place with 13 points from 5 games. 
In the fourth division, Power 22 were 3-1 victors over Rising Sun, Friends of Barclays won 5-nil against Skyline, Maccabi HK were 6-1 winners against Bapcoll, WYFC84 were 3-2 victors over Standard Chartered, Hung Art won 4-1 against Outward Bound, and Scorpions won 1-nil against Darts. 
Scorpions and Friends of Barclays lead the table with 100% records and 15 points from 5 matches, with Maccabi HK third with 12 points from 5 games. 
Allan Jackson has been involved in soccer for more than 40 years as a player, referee, administrator and freelance writer.
